                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">&nbsp;</span>",
                    "content": "<div class=\"methodology\">\n<h1 class=\"methodology-subtitle\">About the data</h1>\n<div class=\"methodology-definitions\">\n<h2>Definitions</h2>\n<p>Percentage of women and girls aged 15 and older who report having experienced at least one occurrence of physical, sexual or psychological violence by a current or former intimate partner during the 12 months previous to the survey.<span class=\"footnote-index\">4</span></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-coverage\">\n<h2>Coverage</h2>\n<p>Women in Mexico aged 15 and older who have ever had an intimate partner: reporting at both the federal and state levels.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-availability\">\n<h2>Availability</h2>\n<p>Information necessary for the computation of this indicator is available at the webpage of the National Institute of Statistics and Geography (INEGI).<span class=\"footnote-index\">5</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n",
